main event: A witness reported seeing rapidly-flashing lights on the horizon for approximately 12 minutes in Silver Spring, Maryland.
interesting points: The lights were observed both visually and on radar., The witness reported that the duration of sighting was longer than it likely was due to difficulty in tracking the object., The lights may have represented multiple objects rather than a single one., The object was noted to be about the size of a saucer and very bright., The report concludes that the data is insufficient to draw firm conclusions about the nature of the sighting.
witness description: Raeburn Winfield Schmidt, who observed the lights from a location in Silver Spring.
